Adversarial review focus:
- Local/offline use: ADR-004 keeps `runtime-local`; ADR-003 keeps Git-readable committed intent.
- Eve outage/API churn: ADR-004 requires fallback policy and P00-T08 public-contract proof before binding defaults.
- Cross-platform operation: ADR-004 inherits adapter capability lessons but keeps execution behind provider-neutral driver interfaces.
- Human approval latency: ADR-005 and ADR-006 place approvals in durable records and outbox gating instead of ad hoc prompts.

